01189 // Combine() allows the user to combine two or more sequences to produce
01190 // values of a Cartesian product of those sequences' elements.
01191 //
01192 // Synopsis:
01193 // Combine(gen1, gen2, ..., genN)
01194 //   - returns a generator producing sequences with elements coming from
01195 //     the Cartesian product of elements from the sequences generated by
01196 //     gen1, gen2, ..., genN. The sequence elements will have a type of
01197 //     tuple<T1, T2, ..., TN> where T1, T2, ..., TN are the types
01198 //     of elements from sequences produces by gen1, gen2, ..., genN.
01199 //
01200 // Combine can have up to 10 arguments. This number is currently limited
01201 // by the maximum number of elements in the tuple implementation used by Google
01202 // Test.
01203 //
01204 // Example:
01205 //
01206 // This will instantiate tests in test case AnimalTest each one with
01207 // the parameter values tuple("cat", BLACK), tuple("cat", WHITE),
01208 // tuple("dog", BLACK), and tuple("dog", WHITE):
01209 //
01210 // enum Color { BLACK, GRAY, WHITE };
01211 // class AnimalTest
01212 //     : public testing::TestWithParam<tuple<const char*, Color> > {...};
01213 //
01214 // TEST_P(AnimalTest, AnimalLooksNice) {...}
01215 //
01216 // INSTANTIATE_TEST_CASE_P(AnimalVariations, AnimalTest,
01217 //                         Combine(Values("cat", "dog"),
01218 //                                 Values(BLACK, WHITE)));
01219 //
01220 // This will instantiate tests in FlagDependentTest with all variations of two
01221 // Boolean flags:
01222 //
01223 // class FlagDependentTest
01224 //     : public testing::TestWithParam<tuple(bool, bool)> > {
01225 //   virtual void SetUp() {
01226 //     // Assigns external_flag_1 and external_flag_2 values from the tuple.
01227 //     tie(external_flag_1, external_flag_2) = GetParam();
01228 //   }
01229 // };
01230 //
01231 // TEST_P(FlagDependentTest, TestFeature1) {
01232 //   // Test your code using external_flag_1 and external_flag_2 here.
01233 // }
01234 // INSTANTIATE_TEST_CASE_P(TwoBoolSequence, FlagDependentTest,
01235 //                         Combine(Bool(), Bool()));
01236 //
